casebody.data:
PAUL S. GALLENA, PROSECUTOR, v. I. GRANT SCOTT, CLERK IN CHANCERY, DEFENDANT. Submitted May 4, 1948 Decided September 9, 1948.

Before Justices Donges and Colie.

For the prosecutor, George Pellettieri. For the defendant, Walter D. Van Riper and Joseph Lanigan. Per Curiam.

The judges being equally divided on the question of whether or not a writ of certiorari should issue, the application must fall.
